This command is used to manage the auto-rebuilding feature of a ddeploy project.

Usage: ddeploy up [option]

Options:
- on: Enable auto-rebuild for the current project.
- off: Disable auto-rebuild for the current project.
- list: List all projects with auto-rebuild enabled.
- -d: Build and run the project in detached mode.
- No option: Build and run the project.

Note:
- Before using the 'on' option, make sure to add the GitHub token using 'doc token [token]'.
- Auto-rebuild enables the project to automatically rebuild and run whenever a new commit is detected in the repository.
- app build with enviorment varaibles from .ddeploy.env and .env (if exist).

